# **✅ PROFILE SECTION SPECIFICATION — ALL TABS**

## **Design Principles Confirmed**

✅ **Simplicity with immediate insightfulness** — Clean, scannable, not redundant  
 ✅ **Keep right sidebar** — Real-time calculations as they type  
 ✅ **Profile always expanded** — No accordion, always visible when data saved  
 ✅ **Selective benchmark badges** — Only where meaningful targets exist  
 ✅ **Card styling** — Border/shadow like Identity screenshot  
 ✅ **Single-dimension focus** — Don't overreach, let Dashboard connect the dots

---

## **BENCHMARK BADGE PHILOSOPHY**

### **What Gets a Badge:**

✅ Metrics with **clear, universal targets** that indicate health  
 ✅ Ratios/percentages that have **industry-standard ranges**  
 ✅ Efficiency indicators where **deviation signals risk**

### **What Doesn't Get a Badge:**

❌ Raw dollar amounts (revenue, AGI, payroll) — **context-dependent**  
 ❌ Counts (team size, client count) — **not performance indicators**  
 ❌ Calculated totals (annual run rate) — **just math, no inherent meaning**  
 ❌ Metrics that require cross-tab context to evaluate

### **Badge Color Logic:**

* 🟢 **Green "Healthy"** — Meets or exceeds target range  
* 🟡 **Yellow "Caution"** — Approaching threshold, monitor  
* 🔴 **Red "Critical"** — Below acceptable range, needs attention

